header
  .content
    p.showcase
      img src="badge.svg"
    h1 Pair widely. Pair often.


section#badge
  .content
    .main-content
      p.lead Put out the pair-programming welcome mat!
      p
        | Put this badge on your blog or project home page. Link it to a way to contact you.
          For instance, link it to a <a href="http://wufoo.com">custom contact form</a>.
            Or use magically generated code with <code>mailto:</code> link.

      form#get-badge-code
        .row.collapse
          .small-12.columns
            button#pick-email.button.active
              | Email
            button#pick-twitter.button
              | Twitter
          .small-9.columns
            input#badge-twitter.hide type="text" placeholder="@AwesomeCoder"
            input#badge-email type="email" placeholder="awesome@coder.org"
          .small-3.columns
            button#submit-email.button.prefix
              | Get badge code!

      textarea.badge-code.hide disabled=true Gode goes here when you submit your email
      p
        | Or link it to your Twitter profile! I don't care! Just put it up, and let the world know it's OK to ask!
    .sidebar-content
      p.lead Get the badge:
      img src="badge.svg"
      p.nb <a href="badge.png">png</a> | <a href="badge.svg">svg</a>

section#resources
  .content
    .main-content
      h2 Resources
      = render 'resources'
    .sidebar-content
      h2 Something Missing?
      p
        | Is this page missing something?
        | <br><a href="https://github.com/avdi/ppwm">Pull requests are welcome!</a>
        | <br>As well as <a href="https://github.com/avdi/ppwm/wiki/Resources">updates to the wiki<a>

